Suggestion: Enhance Context Detection
Enhance the `annotateCalls` method to better detect the context of function calls. This could involve more sophisticated checks to identify when a function is called as a property of an object, especially in cases where the object is newly created. This might require additional logic to track the origin of the function reference and its invocation context. By improving context detection, the method can more accurately annotate function calls, leading to a more correct compilation output.
// Buggy Function
private void annotateCalls(Node n) {
  Preconditions.checkState(n.isCall());

  // Keep track of of the "this" context of a call.  A call without an
  // explicit "this" is a free call.
  Node first = n.getFirstChild();

  // ignore cast nodes.

  if (!NodeUtil.isGet(first)) {
    n.putBooleanProp(Node.FREE_CALL, true);
  }

  // Keep track of the context in which eval is called. It is important
  // to distinguish between "(0, eval)()" and "eval()".
  if (first.isName() &&
      "eval".equals(first.getString())) {
    first.putBooleanProp(Node.DIRECT_EVAL, true);
  }
}
